## 2 Â· Design Principles
| # | Principle | Guidance |
|---|-----|----|
| P1 | **User-Centered** | Every design decision stems from user research, personas, and validated user needs. |
| P2 | **Accessibility First** | Design for WCAG 2.1 AA compliance from day one; consider diverse abilities and contexts. |
| P3 | **Design System Driven** | Maintain consistency through reusable components, tokens, and documented patterns. |
| P4 | **Progressive Enhancement** | Start with core functionality, layer on enhancements for capable devices/browsers. |
| P5 | **Data-Informed Decisions** | Back design choices with user testing, analytics, and performance metrics. |
| P6 | **Mobile-First Responsive** | Design for smallest screens first, scale up gracefully across all viewports. |
